description.narrative:
The Swedish Embassy has together with Denmark and the UNDP been financing the human rights plan of the Ministry of Justice in Burkina Faso, in accordance with the UN recommendations subsequent to the UPR 2013, during 2013-2015. This action plan is to be fully implemented during 2017 when Burkina Faso is to report to the UN on its implementation of the UPR recommendations. During 2013-2015 there has been important progress in the implementation of this action plan for human rights in terms of the following important results:
- Legislation adopted in 2015 to protect women and girls against gender-based violence;
- Legislation against torture adopted in 2015;
- Regional human rights information and documentation centra functioning in all Burkina Faso's regions;
- Strategy developed for the functioning of the National Human Rights Commission, in accordance with the Paris principles for ensuring the independence and financing of the Commission;
- Inter-ministerial commission ensuring the integration of human rights and gender equality in all sectors;
- Rights of the child integrated and ensured in the curricula for primary education;
- Training on human rights provided for teachers, journalists, judges and militaries;
- Regular surveillance of the respect for human rights in Burkina Faso's prisons;
- Special judges trained for defending the rights of children and youth. 

The Swedish funding for 2013-2015 amounts to 8MSEK. However in order to continue the implementation of the human rights action plan in accordance with the UN EPU recommendations additional funding is needed for 2016-2017 in order to increase capacities of the regional human rights centra to document, inform and follow-up on human rights, to ensure the independence and functioning of the National Human Rights Commission, to enhance the respect of human rights of vulnerable groups including in the prisons and for the Ministry to fulfil its role in promoting, coordinating and surveying the respect for human rights.

The action plan proposed for Swedish support for 2016 amount to 5MSEK and an additional 5MSEK is requested for 2017. Hence it is suggested that Sweden adds a total of 10 MSEK for 2016-2017 in addition to the support that amounted to 8 MSEK during 2013-2015, hence amounting to a total Swedish contribution of 18 MSEK to the intervention during the period 2013-2017. The activities described in the detailed work plan for 2016, with its corresponding budget lines, include the production and distribution of additional 500 human rights manuals for primary schools, training and follow-up on human rights training with teachers in all of Burkina Faso's regions, information campaigns in schools to spread knowledge about the regional human rights centra and their services in providing citizens with information on their human rights, social and economic reintegration of women that are accused of with-craft (approximately 40 women currently taken care of at the regional shelter centra sorting under the ministry), accelerated efforts to protect children that are forced to child labour in mining sites (about 30 children having been reintegrated with their families and with their scolarisation assured through the ministry in 2015), maintenance of the offices of the staff at the human rights division of the ministry, collection of data and analysis to provide the report to the UN on the implementation of the UN UPR human rights recommendations, and the conduct of independent and external annual audits, etc.

In 2018, the action plan is submitted to Sweden  and Denmark. An additional 6MSEK was funded by Sweden to the action plan 2018. An amendment of agreement was signed. The activities of the work plan concerned the introduction of human rights education modules in teacher training programs, the elementary Human Rights Education, the sensitization of socio-professional groups on the themes of human rights and civism, strengthen the CEDDH's (centre d'écoute et de documentation sur les droits humains) capacities, the identification of cases of human rights violations and acts of incivism and report them, the sensitization of the populations on the existence and the modalities of implementation of the right to compensation in case of violations or infringements, the treatment and follow-up of human rights violations and report, the implementation of international humanitarian law, the international and regional cooperation participation, participation to the UPR sessions and restitutions, appropriation of the human rights based approach by public actors and local authorities,  re-read the Human Rights Training Manual in 500 copies, awareness of the population on civism and citizenship (freedom to demonstrate), teaching citizenship in formal and non-formal education, operationalization of the National Observatory for Community Conflict Prevention and Management through sensitisation and study of the conflicts situations, improvement and dissemination of statistical information on all areas covered by the human rights conventions, communication and information on ministerial action, implement audit recommendations, improving the accessibility of justice through sensitisation, hold criminal foundations in Diapaga municipality.

The annual narrative, financial and audit reports 2018 are waiting to be received and adopted in the steering committee around October-November 2019.

A new action plan for 2019 is proposed to Sweden and Denmark. An additional 3MSEK will be funded to the split ministry of justice and minitry of human rights action plan 2019. The swedish support will be a continuation. The action plan concerns 4 programs. They are composed of: programme 1 human rights; programme 2 civism and citizenship; programme 3: pilotage and support; programme 4: judiciary administration. Respectively, the different programmes have actions and activities for Sida to finance. The actions and activities are identified on the base of identified problems. They are:

Programme 1: human rights 
Action of education to human rights : activity of three-day training session in Koudougou for 18 permanent teachers of teacher training schools on human rights for their effective teaching in these schools in the framework for the process of transfer of the education to human rights process to the ministry of education ; activity of two training sessions in Ouagadougou and Bobo-Dioulasso of three (03) days for the benefit of 40 permanent teachers of training schools for law enforcement personnel on the consideration of human rights in their teaching ; activity of two workshops for the appropriation of recurrent cases of violations of the category rights of the 2019 - 2021 action plan of the regional directorates ; activity of two-day plea to fifty (50) intellectuals born in the Sahel region for their effective involvement in the fight against the survival of practices, behaviors and considerations that could undermine the dignity of ethnic groups in the Sahel region ; activity of a one-day panel on respect for the right to human dignity for the benefit of fifty (50) community leaders in the Sahel region (sebba) ; activity of training sessions in three (03) regions on the respect of human rights in anti-terrorism operations for the benefit of 75 FDS (Boucle du Mouhoun North and Center-East) ; elaborate the 2018 report on the actions of the "Centre d’écoute et de documentation sur les droits humains - CEDDH".  

Action of regional and international cooperation : elaborate the periodic report under the African Charter on Human and Peoples' Rights; Elaborate the answers to the questionnaires of the special procedures; 

Action of assistance to actors of human rights : Organize a five (05) day appropriation session of the ABDH manual for the benefit of twenty-five (25) Ministry staff in Ouagadougou; Organize a two (2) day training session for 37 local elected officials on the human rights-based approach for its integration into the Boromo communal development plans.

Programme 2 civism and citizenship : 
Action of education to civism and citizenship : Organize a two-day training workshop on citizenship and responsible citizenship for the benefit of 20 delegates from secondary schools in Yako City; Organize eight (08) public awareness skits on roadworthiness and social cohesion for the benefit of four secondary schools in the city of Ouahigouya and four establishments in the city of Gourcy; Organize 5 conferences on civility in secondary schools in the Hauts-Bassins Region; Organize 04 conferences on civility in 04 schools of Ouagadougou; Organize three (03) school-based conferences on citizenship and the freedom to demonstrate; Organize three (03) sensitization sessions on citizen participation for the benefit of 90 local actors from three districts of Ouagadougou ; 

Action of culture of tolerance and peace : Organize six (06) awareness sessions on the values ??of tolerance and peace for the benefit of the populations of six (06) communes of the central region.

Programme 3: pilotage and support: 
Action of human ressources management : Implement the annual tranche of the MDHPC Training Plan. 

Action of information systems and statistics : To elaborate a manual of the database of the treatment of the information of judicial statistics; 

Action of planning, monitoring and evaluation : Develop the 2018 analytical report of the Ministry of Justice, Human Rights and Civic Promotion; Ensure a study trip for the benefit of 5 people on the planning and monitoring evaluation of reforms in the field of justice; To prepare a final report on Sweden's support for the program; Organize a training session on monitoring-evaluation and planning for the benefit of executives of the DGESS of the MDHPC ; 

Action of communication and information on ministerial action : Implement the communication strategy; 

Action of management of material and financial resources : Ensure the maintenance of electrical equipment and installations; Acquire five (5) full desktops and a copier; Acquire specific material (four strong safes) to benefit MDHPC; Ensure the maintenance of rolling stock; Maintain computer and peri-computing equipment for central and deconcentrated structures; Ensure the participation of fifteen (15) DAF staff in the accounting management training seminar; 

Programme 4: judicial administration: 
Action of access to justice : Organize twenty (20) extraordinary judicial hearings; Organize a criminal sitting session in Tenkodogo with 23 files; Organiser une session d'assises criminelles à Diapaga avec 17 dossiers
